attachments.title: What do you call a ‘non-entrepreneur? Cuba’s best hackers
attachments.text: What do you call an innovative person who builds a product out of nothing and launches something that will change people&rsquo;s lives? Everywhere besides Cuba, you&rsquo;d call this person an entrepreneur. You'd never expect in the land of communism, censorship and classic cars that you'd find a hotbed of entrepreneurship. Technically, it doesn&rsquo;t exist. But in my eyes, entrepreneurship is thriving in Cuba.
